      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(trajectory): preserve token usage when truncating oversized trajectory events",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: When a `model.completed` trajectory event exceeds the 256 KB per-event size limit, `truncateOversizedTrajectoryEvent` replaces the entire `data` block with a bare truncation stub — including the `usage` object (~96 bytes). This silently zeros out token/cost accounting for exactly the heaviest turns, where spend is largest.\n- **Root cause**: The truncation logic treats `data` as an indivisible blob and does not extract small structured fields.\n- **Fix**: Extract `usage` from the original event data and carry it forward into the truncation stub. A fallback to the original full-truncation behavior is kept for edge cases.\n- **What did NOT change**: Field-level truncation (`limitTrajectoryPayloadValue`) is untouched. Events that don't exceed the limit are unchanged. The truncation rationale (`truncated`, `originalBytes`, `limitBytes`, `reason`) is unchanged.\n\nCloses #96804\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Scope\n\n- [x] Gateway (trajectory runtime)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** `truncateOversizedTrajectoryEvent` now preserves the `usage` field from the original `data` when replacing oversized event payloads with a truncation stub.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node 24.13.1 on Linux, `node --import tsx` calling the real `createTrajectoryRuntimeRecorder` production function.\n\n**Steps run after the patch:** Created a trajectory runtime recorder, recorded a `model.completed` event with `usage` plus 20 extra 20 KB fields to force event-level truncation, flushed to disk, and inspected the written trajectory line.\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\n=== BEFORE FIX (upstream/main) ===\nEvent-level truncation replaces the entire data block:\n  data: { truncated: true, originalBytes: N, limitBytes: 262144, reason: \"trajectory-event-size-limit\" }\n  usage: LOST — token accounting reads 0 for this turn\n\n=== AFTER FIX (PR branch) ===\nline bytes: 399 (well within the 256 KB limit after truncation)\nevent-level truncated: YES\nusage present: true\nusage: {\"input\":384954,\"output\":5624,\"cacheRead\":333824,\"reasoningTokens\":2038,\"total\":724402}\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix:** Token usage is preserved in the truncation stub when an event is truncated at the event level. The truncated event stays within the 256 KB limit (truncation stub + usage = ~400 bytes).\n\n**Not tested:** Live gateway session with real model interaction producing a `model.completed` event that exceeds 256 KB. The event-level truncation path is verified via the real production functions `createTrajectoryRuntimeRecorder` + `recordEvent` + `flush`.\n\n## Security Impact\n\n- New permissions? No\n- Secrets handling changed? No\n- New network calls? No\n",
        "branch": "fix/96804-trajectory-preserve-usage",
